he festive reversal of sex roles and political order, and the ritualistic and dramatic structure of religious riots. The final two essays discuss the impact of printing on the quasi-literate, and the collecting of common proverbs and medical folklore by learned students of the "people" during the Ancien Régime. The book includes eight pages of illustrations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503621183423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503621183/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles